<p/>


<p/>
<b>Shill</b> updates syntax files for a variety of editors used for 
Linden Scripting Language (LSL) code.  With these files, you'll enjoy proper
syntax highlighting in your favorite editor.  <i>New in this version</i>: the 
Shill keyword lists are now based on source files from the Second Life client.


<p/>
Included here are files I found
at the
<a href="http://wiki.secondlife.com/wiki/LSL_Alternate_Editors">
LSL Alternate Editors</a>
page at the 
<a href="http://wiki.secondlife.com/wiki/LSL_Portal">
LSL Portal</a>,
along with some I saw mentioned in various forums.
My sincere thanks to all syntax file authors. I've included the origin
of each file if known.

Follow the instructions at the Wiki for installation, including updated files
from here as appropriate.

<p/>
See below for more
details on the automated process that generates these files.
Please contact me with comments,
suggestions, and requests to update these or other syntax files.  You are also invited
to discuss
<b>Shill</b>
at the <a href="http://forums.secondlife.com/showthread.php?t=108821">
Second Life Forums</a>. 

<br/>

<p/>
<i>elsewhere in the Marker network:</i> Interested in command line image upload?  Try
<a href="http://adammarker.org/redcap">redcap</a>
