<table summary="LSL files hosted at shill" bgcolor="#8888FF" cellspacing="6" cellpadding="6" rules="rows">

	<tr>
		<td><b>the Shill master files</b></td>
		<td><a href="keywords.yaml"
			onClick="pageTracker._trackEvent('download', 'shill', 'keywords.yaml');"
			>keywords.yaml</a>
		<br/>
		<a href="signatures.yaml"
		onClick="pageTracker._trackEvent('download', 'shill', 'signatures.yaml');"
		>signatures.yaml</a>
		<br/><br/>
		<a href="shill.rb"
			onClick="pageTracker._trackEvent('download', 'shill', 'shill.rb');"
			>shill.rb</a>
		<br/>	
		</td>
		<td>
		Shill's master lists of functions, events, and constants.  They are formatted
		using
		<a href="http://yaml.org">YAML</a>, a simple markup language.
		
		<ul>
		<li><b><em>keywords</em></b> contains just the event, function, and constant names.</li>
		
		<li><b><em>signatures</em></b> has signatures and short help
		for functions and events
		(currently only used by SciTE-ez).
		See <em>implementation notes</em> below for more details.</li>
		
		<li><b><em>shill.rb</em></b>
		reads the YAML files and inserts the keyword lists into the
		editor configuration files.</li>
		</ul>
		</td>
	</tr>	

</table>
